name: Katong Yong Tau Foo

reviews.text: a familiar face in katong shopping centre, been patronising since i was a young child. soup is light yet flavourful, some interesting fried options as well. fried food are always separated from the soup! their rojak is also super good, fried items are always toasted well and never stale and soggy

Don‚Äôt let the environment deceive you, the Rojak prices are in SGD 4.5 6 8 portions and I ordered the SGD 6 to sample.

My my my I am pleasantly surprised as this stall takes its youtiao Ê≤πÊù° very seriously, the chef a seasoned one deep fried the youtiao, and the prawn paste sauce is superbly fragrant and delicious as it‚Äôs really the true original authentic taste of Rojak seasoning, the cucumber crispy, pineapple fresh, turnip fresh, it would be perfect if they put bean sprouts, the peanut is generous and the prawn paste sauce is superb! I classify this as the 5 out of 5 star traditional authentic cuisines of Singapore!

If you have Singaporeans elderlies, and visitors, bring them here for their tastebuds confirmation and dispel the curiosity of our foreign friends of Singapore.

One of the best yongtaufoo I‚Äôve tried in SG! Costing $0.8 per piece, it is reasonable considering the ingredients are very fresh! My favourite items are the fried yam, eggplant, and the ladies finger! Soup and laksa gravy is so goodüòã

Taken the yong tau foo laska. Laska gravy is nice and well prepared with dried shrimp and coconut milk. The gravy is more towards sweet than savoury. The fried yong tau foo tends to go better with the laska than the non-fried one.

Really fantastic Yong Tau Foo. Wide range of ingredients to choose from and always cooked to perfection in their self made broth. The secret sweet sauce and chilli really makes the dishes taste great. Definitely a must eat!
